The purpose of this assignment is to ensure that you are able to use
Git and Scala.

Instructions
============

1. Clone this repo.

2. Create a new repo for your homeworks in the course organization.
   Name your repo `TYY-user-USERNAME`, where,
   - `T` is one charcter for the term: `f` Fall or `s` for Spring,
   - `YY` is the two digit year, e.g. `19` for 2019,
   - `USERNAME` is your github username.

3. Change the remote for your cloned repo to your newly created user
   repo.

4. Write your name and Mines CWID in the AUTHORS file.

5. Edit the `.gitignore` file to ignore JVM class files and any
   temporary or backup files that your editor may generate.

6. Under the `hw01` directory in the repo, implement the "Hello World"
   Scala program covered in lecture.

7. Push all above changes to your user repo in the github.com course
   organization.

8. Submit via Canvas a screenshot showing the compilation and
   execution of your "Hello World" program.

Grading
=======

| Item                          | Points |
|-------------------------------|--------|
| Correctly-named User Repo     | 5      |
| AUTHORS file                  | 5      |
| .gitignore / no cruft in repo | 5      |
| "Hello World" code            | 5      |
| Screenshot                    | 5      |
